	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=17207&amp;mid=108334788546837">Group weapon vs Raid Weapon</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=17207&amp;mid=108334788546837#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Fri, Apr 30th 1:58 PM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=108438"><span id="Sage">Master Aeldwan</span></a><br /><b><span id="Sage">Sage</span></b><br /><span id="notbold">63 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.68]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Actually this weapon is great for a rogue in a regular group with a good agro tank. My warrior can easily keep agro from most good rogues and even for the 2-3secs the mob might turn around on a hi DPS rogue the mobs aren't swinging for enough for the rogue to care in a normal group. Solid DPS, proc is damaging and useful in that it stacks with near everything and has a nice AC debuff component. <br/>I would not however recommend using it in a Raid situation because it is far closer to the margin for a rogue with wonderful Damage output to have that mob turn off the MA because of a higher agro proc like this.<br/>In order the best agro procs are stuns, AC debuffs, resist debuffs, other debuffs, healing/rune effects, damage. A proc that does both a debuff effect and damage like this, or stun and damage like Ykesha and Force Strike weapons, grabs very nice agro. I used both a Honed Obsidian Dagger and a CHoS and despite the slightly better damage/delay on the CHoS the dagger was VERY close for keeping agro.<br/>Lastly this weapon has a nice proc timing bonus that means it's &quot;casting time&quot; for its proc is smaller than that of some weapons. It can actually go off slightly more often than the CHoS; another good reason to look at it for possible Tank agro. Still its just a decent dagger for Warrior's. I'd much prefer to see it in the hands of someone that will get more common use out of it despite how much of a DPS upgrade it would be for mine ;}<br/>Again, great toy for groups, not so great for mainhand when raiding, decent offhander if you don't have something that procs a touch less often for more damage.<br/><br/><em id=fs8>Edited, Fri Apr 30 14:03:20 2004</em></p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br /><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=397227 target=akztarg>Dutchess Buddercup Voxslayer</a><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=310389 target=akztarg>Master Aeldwan the Coercer</a> <br/>Primal Evolution, Morell-Thule<br/>"Doing the improbable daily to make the impossible seem easy"</td></tr>
